narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Intermediate level understanding of Indonesian. Movement into noun/verb forms.
You will learn a ton about the Indonesian language.
Knowledge of Indonesian language and culture.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: It is a little disorganized, but it is overall not only a learning environment, but also an enjoyable experience. I learn much better in this style of teaching through talking. Rather than have specific guidelines, you are prompted to speak and learn as you go along, which I feel is the best way to truly begin to understand a language.
Bu is the absolute best. She is always positive and cares more for her students than any other professor I've had at Yale.
I like this course however it could be organized better

Strengths: immersion in Indonesian culture in food music dance and other Weaknesses: given very short notice for tests. Extremely long vocab lists of words very briefly mentioned during lecture given to us about 2 days before the test. Study guides and test expectations given with no alert and very late. Unorganized

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. Not only do you get the opportunity to learn a new language, but you also get a chance to experience and learn about Indonesian culture.
Trust me - this is the best class.
Yes! Indo is hands down the best thing about Yale.
